<div class="layer backdrop whiteout"></div>
<div class="layer controls">
    <form class="popout">
        <a class="close" href="javascript: void 0">&times;</a>
        <p>If you were the human that defined matrix addition, how would you define it?</p>
        <p>For matrices <code>A</code> and <code>B</code>, choose a result for <code>A + B</code> from the options below.</p>
        <div class="equation">
        <code>
            A =
            \begin{bmatrix}
            3 & -1 \\
            2 & 0
            \end{bmatrix}
            \hspace{20pt}
            B =
            \begin{bmatrix}
            -7 & 2 \\
            3 & 5
            \end{bmatrix}
        </code>
        </div>

        <label class="radio inline">
            <input type="radio" name="answer" value="0">
            <code>
                A' =
                \begin{bmatrix}
                -4 & 1 \\
                5 & 5
                \end{bmatrix}
            </code>
        </label>
        <label class="radio inline">
            <input type="radio" name="answer" value="1">
            <code>
                B' =
                \begin{bmatrix}
                8 & 2 \\
                4 & -7
                \end{bmatrix}
            </code>
        </label>
        <label class="radio inline">
            <input type="radio" name="answer" value="2">
            <code>
                C =
                \begin{bmatrix}
                3 & -1 & -7 & 2 \\
                2 & 0 & 3 & 5
                \end{bmatrix}
            </code>
        </label>
        <label class="radio inline">
            <input type="radio" name="answer" value="3">
            <code>
                D =
                \begin{bmatrix}
                3 & -1 \\
                2 & 0 \\
                -7 & 2 \\
                3 & 5
                \end{bmatrix}
            </code>
        </label>

        {{>submit-area}}
    </form>
</div>
